                "message": "Fix marking async gen as not running in athrow_throw\n\nThis was another thing marked as dodgy in @devdanzin's analysis.\nThe description is\n\n> When athrow_throw encounters StopAsyncIteration/GeneratorExit in aclose() mode, it doesn't reset ag_running_async=0 or agt_state=CLOSED, unlike the identical path in athrow_send_impl (line 884-885). The generator is permanently stuck in \"running_async\" state, causing subsequent operations to fail with \"asynchronous generator is already running.\"\n\nThis looks correct, but I don't really understand async generators well\nenough to really know.\nEssentially, I've copied the code from https://github.com/python/cpython/commit/7d369d471cf2b067c4d795d70b75201c48b46f5b\nI've also taken as much as possible to of the tests added by that\nPR (and confirmed that they do fail without the patch). In both\ncases I've taken the version in the current main branch of\nCPython rather than using that PR exactly. Some of the\n`TestUnawaitedWarnings` tests are disabled because\nthey don't currently work - I think we need other changes from\nelsewhere.",
